ANC Western Cape secretary Faiez Jacobs appeared in the Cape Town magistrates court earlier where he was accused of assaulting former ANC researcher Wesley Seale in 2015. CAPE TOWN - ANC Western Cape secretary Faiez Jacobs is a free man after a court discharged him of assault charges.Jacobs appeared in the Cape Town magistrates court earlier where he was accused of assaulting former ANC researcher Wesley Seale back in 2015.The court found the State's case was too poor to proceed with prosecution. Jacobs has always maintained he acted in self-defence after he was attacked by Seale.